   434	### `.github/workflows/ci.yml` — new `compose-smoke` job
   435	
   436	```yaml
   437	  compose-smoke:
   438	    name: compose-smoke
   439	    runs-on: ubuntu-latest
   440	    steps:
   441	      - uses: actions/checkout@v4
   442	      - name: Verify docker compose + jq are available
   443	        run: |
   444	          docker compose version
   445	          jq --version
   446	      - name: Run compose smoke
   447	        working-directory: reference/compose
   448	        run: bash healthcheck/smoke.sh
   449	```
   450	
   451	GitHub Actions' `ubuntu-latest` runners ship with Docker, the
   452	Compose v2 plugin, and `jq` pre-installed; no extra setup needed.
   453	The README's prerequisites section also lists `jq` so local users
   454	who need to run `smoke.sh` outside CI know to install it.
   455	
